-- EditorClient — the legacy Data Editor (backtick `) — RETIRED 2026-07-02.
--
-- Superseded by EditorClientV2 (backslash \), the rebuilt record-driven editor. This stub is
-- intentionally inert: it builds no UI, binds no key (the backtick ` is now free), and adds no
-- ProvinceInteraction select listener. It stays mapped in default.project.json so the ScreenGui's
-- EditorClient LocalScript syncs to this no-op instead of leaving the old code live in the place.
--
-- WHY RETIRED
-- V1 decided whether a clicked tile was "seeded" from `eu4Map` membership. In the post-collapse v4
-- world, `eu4Map` is a legacy bridge that only ever covered the original 2798 provinces; the 2915
-- AI-generated provinces have full, persisted province records (all 5713 provinces are seeded in the
-- v4 DataStore) but no `eu4Map` entry, so V1 falsely reported them "unseeded" and refused to reassign
-- their owner. `eu4Map` is not read by any runtime system in collapsed mode (ProvinceStamper resolves
-- each part directly by province id — see ProvinceStamper.resolvePartId), so rather than keep patching
-- V1's stale check we retire the editor. EditorClientV2 decides "seeded" from the province record
-- (`snapshot.provinces[province_id] ~= nil`) and handles all 5713 provinces correctly.
--
-- NOT CARRIED OVER
-- The only V1-unique action was "Export to Lua" (the `exportToLua` command — write in-editor edits back
-- to the Data/*.luau source modules). It is vestigial in DataStore-authoritative v4 (source modules do
-- not drive runtime province/country data) and was intentionally left behind. The full V1 implementation
-- remains in git history (pre-2026-07-02) if that export ever needs porting into V2.
